headline: Why Ulta (ULTA) Stock Is Up Today
summary: Shares of beauty, cosmetics, and personal care retailer Ulta Beauty (NASDAQ:ULTA) jumped 7.1% in the afternoon session after peer, Bath & Body Works, reported strong third-quarter financial results. BBWI outperformed analysts' expectations for sales and earnings, and its guidance for the next quarter also surpassed consensus estimates. summary: Bath & Body Works (BBWI) delivered earnings and revenue surprises of 6.52% and 1.99%, respectively, for the quarter ended October 2024. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?
